
Err:
Show breakdown of costs

USAGE
  c3x breakdown [flags]

EXAMPLES
  Use Terraform directory:

      c3x breakdown --path /code --terraform-var-file my.tfvars

  Use Terraform plan JSON:

      terraform plan -out tfplan.binary
      terraform show -json tfplan.binary > plan.json
      c3x breakdown --path plan.json

FLAGS
      --budget float                 Monthly cost budget in configured currency. Exits with code 1 if exceeded
      --budget-increase float        Maximum allowed cost increase percentage for diff. Exits with code 1 if exceeded
      --config-file string           Path to C3X config file. Cannot be used with path, terraform* or usage-file flags
      --exclude-path strings         Paths of directories to exclude, glob patterns need quotes
      --fields strings               Comma separated list of output fields: all,price,monthlyQuantity,unit,hourlyCost,monthlyCost.
                                     Supported by table and html output formats (default [monthlyQuantity,unit,monthlyCost])
      --format string                Output format: json, table, html (default "table")
  -h, --help                         help for breakdown
      --include-all-paths            Set project auto-detection to use all subdirectories in given path
      --no-cache                     Don't attempt to cache Terraform plans
      --offline                      Use local pricing database instead of remote API (run 'c3x pricing sync' first)
      --out-file string              Save output to a file, helpful with format flag
  -p, --path string                  Path to the Terraform directory or JSON/plan file
      --project-name string          Name of project in the render. Defaults to path or git repo name
      --recommend                    Show cost optimization recommendations after estimate
      --show-skipped                 List unsupported resources
      --sync-usage-file              Sync usage-file with missing resources, needs usage-file too (experimental)
      --terraform-var stringArray    Set value for an input variable, similar to Terraform's -var flag
      --terraform-var-file strings   Load variable files, similar to Terraform's -var-file flag. Provided files must be relative to the --path flag
      --terraform-workspace string   Terraform workspace to use. Applicable when path is a Terraform directory
      --usage-file string            Path to C3X usage file that specifies values for usage-based resources
      --what-if stringArray          Override resource attributes for scenario analysis (e.g., 'aws_instance.web.instance_type=m6i.xlarge')

GLOBAL FLAGS
      --debug-report       Generate a debug report file which can be sent to C3X team
      --log-level string   Log level (trace, debug, info, warn, error, fatal)
      --no-color           Turn off colored output

Error: --config-file flag cannot be used with the following flags: --path, --project-name, --terraform-*
